#. type: Title ==
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:28
#, no-wrap
msgid "Project Goal"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:31
msgid ""
"As FreeBSD's userbase has grown, the number of people who want to donate "
"materials or funds to the Project has grown. The Donations Liaison is "
"intended to streamline the handling of these donations, and to ensure that "
"they are handled in a timely and reasonable manner."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:33
#, no-wrap
msgid "Donations Liaison Charter"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:36
msgid ""
"The purpose of the Donations Liaison Office is to encourage and guide "
"donations according to a set of community-accepted rules. The DLO has the "
"following responsibilities."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:38
msgid "to establish and maintain a clear set of procedures for handling donations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:39
msgid "to respond to donation offers in a timely manner."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:40
msgid ""
"to maintain a list of equipment and resources desired by the FreeBSD "
"community."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:41
msgid "to coordinate donation offers with the FreeBSD developer community."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:42
msgid "to shepherd donations through the entire donation process."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:43
msgid ""
"to work with a small team to ensure a timely, informed, and correct response "
"is available at all times."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:44
msgid "to publicly acknowledge donors and donations when the donation is complete."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:45
msgid "record the status of all loans to the Project."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:46
msgid "provide open records of all donations to the FreeBSD developer community."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:48
#, no-wrap
msgid "Donating to the FreeBSD Project"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:51
msgid ""
"So, you want to donate something to the FreeBSD Project? Great! We strongly "
"rely upon user donations to accomplish our goals. Please read below to see "
"how to contact us about your donation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:53
msgid ""
"If you don't know what you want to give, take a look at our "
"https://wiki.freebsd.org/Donations/WantList[list of needs]. We would "
"appreciate any items on this list. If you have equipment you'd like to "
"donate, read on."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:55
#, no-wrap
msgid "Tax Credit for Donations"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:58
msgid ""
"The FreeBSD Foundation can act as a charitable organization for tax "
"purposes. If you live in the United States, your donation can be deducted "
"from your taxes under certain conditions. If you want a receipt for tax "
"purposes your contribution, please let us know when you send information on "
"your donation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:60
msgid ""
"A tax credit is not as easy as it might seem. The donations team must be "
"informed of the desire for a tax deduction so the foundation may be "
"notified, and informed when it has been shipped. The Foundation will also "
"need to know when the item has been received by the intended individual. The "
"Foundation must then be able to demonstrate that the donation is in the "
"_public good_. All of this together means that while we probably have "
"developers who would be interested in that big box of ISA cards in your "
"closet, you probably cannot get a tax credit for them; the total work needed "
"to process, ship, and document them far exceeds their total value."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:62
msgid ""
"The FreeBSD Foundation will provide a receipt for delivery of "
"equipment. They will not, however, provide a fair-market valuation of the "
"equipment -- in fact, the law forbids them to do so. We recommend checking "
"elsewhere for valuations of hardware donations. Since many of our donations "
"are obsolete, making fair market value hard to judge, we suggest searching "
"on Ebay or other used equipment sites for prices paid for similar equipment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:64
msgid ""
"To receive a tax receipt for a donation, you will need to complete a "
"https://www.freebsdfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Hardware-Donation-Form.pdf[Hardware "
"Donation Form] from the FreeBSD Foundation website."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:65
#, no-wrap
msgid "How to Donate"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:68
msgid ""
"Part of the goal of the Donations Liaison Office is to match donations with "
"developers who can use them. We don't accept just any donation; we only "
"handle those that have a home with a developer who can use them to improve "
"FreeBSD. This saves time all around, and also helps assure donors that what "
"their contributions are actually supporting the FreeBSD Project. The down "
"side is that we need some information about your donation before accepting "
"it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:70
msgid "Donations generally fall into three categories:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:72
msgid "<<#money,Financial>>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:73
msgid "<<#systems,Complete Computers>>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:74
msgid "<<#components,Computer Components>>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:76
msgid ""
"If you have something to offer that doesn't fall into one of these "
"categories, don't fret! Just contact us at donations@FreeBSD.org with your "
"offer. Just because it's not the run-of-the-mill offer doesn't mean that "
"we're not interested."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:78
#, no-wrap
msgid "Financial Contributions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:81
msgid ""
"The FreeBSD Project does not directly accept financial contributions. A "
"sponsor organization, the https://www.freebsdfoundation.org[FreeBSD "
"Foundation], accepts financial contributions for us. Please see their Web "
"site for details on financial contributions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:83
#, no-wrap
msgid "Complete Computer Systems"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:86
msgid ""
"The FreeBSD Project always needs computers. If you have a computer that you "
"would like to donate to the Project, please contact us with the following "
"information:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:88
msgid "Hardware specifications: architecture, motherboard, CPU, disk space, memory."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:89
msgid ""
"Does this system currently run FreeBSD, or is it unsupported? If possible, "
"please attach a dmesg from a FreeBSD install on this system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:90 content/en/donations/_index.adoc:102
msgid "Are you willing to ship this system?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:91 content/en/donations/_index.adoc:103
msgid ""
"Your physical location. We try to make shipping as easy and inexpensive as "
"possible."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:92
msgid ""
"Also mention if you want a <<#taxcredit,tax credit>> for this system. (Note "
"that not all donations can realistically receive a tax credit, as the cost "
"of supplying the credit may exceed the value of the donation.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:94
#, no-wrap
msgid "Computer Components"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:97
msgid ""
"If you have hardware that you would like to donate to the Project, please "
"contact us with the following information:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:99
msgid ""
"The hardware description: model, part number, manufacturer, etc. If you have "
"an exact link to the manufacturer's Web page for this component, that would "
"be helpful."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:100
msgid "Is this hardware currently supported in FreeBSD?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:101
msgid ""
"What documentation do you have? A piece of hardware is not sufficient to "
"write a driver; driver authors need detailed chipset data from the "
"manufacturer. (Don't worry too much if you don't have this documentation, as "
"it may be available elsewhere.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:104
msgid ""
"Also mention if you want a <<#taxcredit,tax credit>> for this "
"hardware. (Note that not all donations can realistically receive a tax "
"credit, as the cost of supplying the credit may exceed the value of the "
"donation.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:105
#, no-wrap
msgid "What we Do with this Information"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:108
msgid ""
"Once we have a description of the donation, the Donations Liaison Office "
"will contact the developer community and offer the resource to them. If we "
"have a developer who would like the item, we put the donor and the recipient "
"in contact and let them work out shipping information. If there are multiple "
"developers interested in a resource, we try to learn what each developer "
"would use the resource for and allocate it most effectively for the "
"Project. If no developer is interested, we turn down the offer."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/donations/_index.adoc:109
msgid ""
"Our goal is to place (or decline) all donations within 7 days of receipt of "
"complete information."
msgstr ""
